  "body": "### Description\nWhen there is very high contention for disk IOPs, Teku's performance may suffer, including reduced attestation effectiveness but particularly an inability to catch up to the chain head when syncing. Since Teku is functioning correctly but is bottlenecked by the slow disk access, there are no indications in the logs to indicate why sync is progressing so slowly.\n\nWe should investigate ways to identify when database access is slow and log warnings. Threshold for raising the alerts should likely be fairly high as we really just want to highly when disk speed is causing significant issues, to the point of it appearing that Teku isn't working.  Metrics can be used to investigate less significant issues.",
